:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19119,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/05\/12\/maintain-relations-kuffar-family\/","url_meta":{"origin":36478,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Family: The Prophet does not cut off unbelieving relatives","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 12, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"'Amr ibn al-\u2018As reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, the relatives\u00a0of my father are not my allies. Verily, only Allah and the righteous believers are my allies. Yet, they have the bonds of kinship and I will uphold their family ties.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 5990,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":36476,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/06\/01\/silat-al-rahim-rizq\/","url_meta":{"origin":36478,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Rahim: Increase your lifespan, expand provision","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 1, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"\u2018Uqbah ibn \u2018Amir reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \"Surely, whoever wants to extend his lifespan and expand his provision, let him uphold his family ties.\u201d Source: Shu\u2019ab al-Ima\u0304n 7587 Grade: Sahih li ghayrihi (authentic due to external evidence) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064f\u0642\u0652\u0628\u064e\u0629\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":36951,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/09\/16\/duties-to-household\/","url_meta":{"origin":36478,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Family: Duties to household more important than voluntary worship","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 16, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Wahb ibn Jabir reported: The client of Abdullah ibn Amr, may Allah be pleased with him, said to him, \u201cI intend to reside this month by the Sacred House in Jerusalem.\u201d Abdullah said to him, \u201cHave you left your family with enough to sustain themselves?\u201d He said no. Abdullah said,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/36478","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=36478"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/36478\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.